# Orka — AI-Powered Semantic Code Surgery

Orka is installed as an editable pip package in this project's virtual environment (`env/`).

## When to Use Orka vs Direct Edit

| Scenario | Use |
|----------|-----|
| Refactoring a method body (10+ lines) | Orka |
| Extracting a class to a new file | Orka |
| Generating tests for a method | Orka |
| Understanding dependencies before a change | Orka inspect |
| Tiny fix (1-3 lines, typo, log level) | Direct edit |
| Scaffolding a brand-new file | Direct edit |

## Commands

```bash
# Scan the codebase (run first, or after major changes)
orka scan

# Inspect dependencies
orka inspect --id "File:src/app.py"
orka inspect --id "Class:myproject.models.User"
orka inspect --id "Method:module.Class.method"

# Refactor a method (AST-safe, preserves signatures)
orka refactor --file src/app.py --cls MyService --method handle_order --req "add validation"
orka refactor --file src/app.py --method standalone_func --req "add error handling"
orka refactor --file src/app.py --method foo --req "..." --dry-run  # preview

# Generate tests
orka testgen --file src/app.py --method process --output tests/test_process.py --run
orka testgen --file src/app.py --method process --n 3 --output tests/test_process.py  # 3 tests

# Extract a class (auto-heals imports across project)
orka extract --file src/utils.py --cls OldClass --dest src/models/old_class.py

# Check health
orka doctor

# View feedback (self-hardening insights)
orka feedback
```

## MCP Integration

Orka exposes tools via MCP for structured IDE integration. Add to your MCP config:

```json
{
  "orka": {
    "type": "local",
    "command": ["env/bin/python", "-m", "orka.mcp.server"],
    "enabled": true
  }
}
```

Available MCP tools: `orka_scan`, `orka_inspect`, `orka_refactor`, `orka_testgen`, `orka_extract`, `orka_doctor`.

## Architecture

- **4-Gate Validation**: Every LLM output passes snippet AST → assembly → file AST → pytest before disk
- **LibCST Surgery**: Preserves signatures, decorators, formatting — no string replacement
- **Dependency Graph**: NetworkX graph of all files, classes, methods, imports
- **Semantic Search**: ChromaDB vector search for similar code examples
- **Fix Loop**: Failed validations trigger LLM repair (up to 3 iterations) with rollback on failure
